HEADWORD: Canonicals
<hw>Ca*non"ic*als</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <def>The dress
prescribed by canon{2} to be worn by a clergyman when officiating.
Sometimes, any distinctive professional dress.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Full canonicals</b></col>, <cd>the complete costume of an
officiating clergyman or ecclesiastic.</cd></cs></p>

<p><ent>Canonicate</ent>⟦br⟧
